  "Allegations" : "SEC LITIGATION RELEASE 21255, OCTOBER 16, 2009: THE SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION (\"COMMISSION\") FILED A COMPLAINT AGAINST DANIELLE CHIESI ALLEGING VIOLATIONS OF SECTION 17(A) OF THE SECURITIES ACT OF 1933 (\"SECURITIES ACT\") AND SECTION 10(B) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 (\"EXCHANGE ACT\") AND RULE 10B-5 THEREUNDER.  THE COMMISSION ALLEGED THAT CHIESI ENGAGED IN A MASSIVE INSIDER TRADING SCHEME THAT GENERATED MORE THAN $25 MILLION IN ILLICIT GAINS.  CHIESI OBTAINED INSIDE INFORMATION FROM AN EXECUTIVE AT ANOTHER COMPANY AND TRADED ON THE INFORMATION ON BEHALF OF A FUND OF HER COMPANY, NETTING A PROFIT OF APPROXIMATELY $2.4 MILLION.  CHIESI ALSO PASSED ON THE INSIDE INFORMATION TO ANOTHER INDIVIDUAL, WHO THEN TRADED ON BEHALF OF HIS OWN COMPANY.  THE COMMISSION ALSO ALLEGED THAT ANOTHER INDIVIDUAL PROVIDED INSIDE INFORMATION TO CHIESI ABOUT A COMPANY.  THE OTHER INDIVIDUAL OBTAINED THE INFORMATION WHEN HIS COMPANY WAS CONTEMPLATING ACQUIRING THE OTHER COMPANY.  THE COMMISSION ALLEGED THAT CHIESI THEN TRADED ON THE BASIS OF THIS INFORMATION ON BEHALF OF HER COMPANY, MAKING APPROXIMATELY $1 MILLION IN PROFITS.  SEC LITIGATION RELEASE 21284, NOVEMBER 5, 2009: ON NOVEMBER 5, 2009, THE SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION FILED AN AMENDED COMPLAINT, NAMING 13 ADDITIONAL DEFENDANTS.  THE COMMISSION FURTHER ALLEGED THAT CHIESI USED INFORMATION ABOUT EARNINGS, TRANSACTIONS, TAKEOVERS AND JOINT VENTURES OBTAINED FROM NEWLY NAMED DEFENDANTS TO TRADE ON HER COMPANY'S BEHALF.  SHE ALSO PASSED THE INFORMATION TO OTHER INDIVIDUALS.",
